  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Normally, when you refer to someone being in a camp or in a prison or something like that, you talk about seven years, eight years, nine years, and that's a terrible situation.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, again, I just want to say that-- that a year in a concentration camp, two years in a concentration camp, is just a complete miracle of a person to survive.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And bringing me back to Dachau, in Dachau, as I indicated, was a place that we, again, were now, as I know it today, why we went to Dachau, that was already the order for the final solution.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that point, we were no longer needed in camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The German Reich was in a disarray, and at best, at that particular juncture-- this is already late, early '45-- and the Russians were-- were doing their thing on one front, and, of course, the Allies were doing very well on the other front.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the order was to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as expediently as possible to eliminate and destroy us as fast as they could.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was taken out of-- I was in Dachau for about two or three weeks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Dachau was so full with people, of all kinds, with prisoners, and so on, that they moved us to a little annex which was about two or three kilometers down the street-- down the street, or down the road, or down-- outside of Munich called Allach.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in Allach, I was liberated, but in a very [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] different fashion.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "About May-- about May of-- of-- of '45, we started hearing artillery shells bombarding our barracks and our camp of Allach.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
